10
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:49,120
Let us return to the spectrum of
the binding energy per nucleon

11
00:00:49,120 --> 00:00:51,080
as a function on the mass number A.

12
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:58,170
We see that there is a maximum for
A = 60 around iron.

13
00:00:58,170 --> 00:00:59,750
For lighter nuclei,

14
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:06,170
the dependence of the binding energy on
A is much stronger than for heavier nuclei.

15
00:01:06,170 --> 00:01:11,070
Light nuclei are generally
less strongly bound except for

16
00:01:11,070 --> 00:01:15,860
the double magic nuclei,
like for instance He-4,

17
00:01:15,860 --> 00:01:18,620
and their binding energy
increases faster with A.

18
00:01:20,060 --> 00:01:26,200
One can therefore use this strong
variation of binding energy with respect

19
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:32,720
to the mass number of light nuclei
